headline: Has Intel’s 79.8% 2025 Surge Outrun Its Fundamentals?
summary: If you are wondering whether Intel is still a bargain after its huge run, or if the easy money has already been made, you are in the right place to unpack what the current share price really implies. Despite a choppy week with the stock down about 2.6%, Intel is still up roughly 5.4% over the last month and an impressive 79.8% year to date, reshaping how the market is pricing its turnaround story. That surge has been fueled by renewed optimism in Intel's foundry ambitions, ongoing...
